				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Possible new /disc bug<a name="52820"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 20 04 12:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>when combat abilities were first introduced, a lovely bug came about.
<br />

<br />
if you placed the discs on your combat window (ctrl+ 1-8), and then hit a regular hotkey 1-8, you could end up firing the disc/ability. (1 = ctrl+1, 2=ctrl+2, etc even without hitting ctrl).
<br />

<br />
to combat this glitch, i place the abilities on the 5-8 slots (do not use hybrid UI for alt c window &gt;.&lt; ), as i do the majority of my twisting on 1-4, with FM on 0. for the warrior, i had to put them *all* on another hotkey bank. that's a pain, let me tell you.
<br />

<br />
now with every melee class, i only leave the combat window up to click off abilities early as &quot;accidental misfires&quot; are draining on the small endurance pools.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
